<!-- Slide 44: Cross-Cultural Communication Introduction -->
<div class="slide">
    <h1>Cross-Cultural Communication Excellence</h1>
    <h2>Bridging Indian and Western Business Cultures</h2>
    
    <div class="highlight-box">
        <h3>Why This Matters at Stride Logistics</h3>
        <p>We serve global clients across continents. Understanding cultural nuances in communication can make the difference between securing a $10 million contract and losing it to cultural misunderstandings.</p>
    </div>
    
    <h3>Cultural Communication Impacts</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Client relationships:</strong> Building trust across cultures</li>
        <li><strong>Team collaboration:</strong> Working with international colleagues</li>
        <li><strong>Negotiation success:</strong> Understanding different business styles</li>
        <li><strong>Career advancement:</strong> Succeeding in global organizations</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>The Cultural Iceberg Model</h3>
    <div style="text-align: center; margin: 20px 0;">
        <p><strong>Visible (10%):</strong> Language, customs, food</p>
        <p><strong>Hidden (90%):</strong> Values, assumptions, communication styles</p>
    </div>
</div>

